panels.title: NR_5054b 5G Initial BLER in downlink transmissions in PDSCH / Init BLER DL PDSCH tx [%]

panels.description:
This KPI shows the residual Block Error Ratio (BLER) for PDSCH. Residual BLER is defined as the ratio between the number of failed transmissions after the MAX HARQ retransmission reached and the number of packets to transmit, that is, the 1st HARQ transmissions.
In real-time monitoring, the HARQ feedback might be received in a different measurement period than the initial transmission. For that reason, the initial transmissions in the formula are calculated as the successful transmissions plus the unsuccessful transmissions.
HARQ feedback DTX is considered as unsuccessful.

panels.title: NR_5056d 5G Initial BLER in PUSCH / UL init BLER PUSCH [%]

panels.description:
This KPI shows the residual Block Error Ratio (BLER) for PUSCH. Residual BLER is defined as the ratio between the number of failed transmissions after the MAX HARQ retransmission reached and the number of packets to transmit, that is, the 1st HARQ transmissions.
In real-time monitoring, the HARQ feedback might be received in a different measurement period than the initial transmission. For that reason, the initial transmissions in the formula are calculated as the successful transmissions plus the unsuccessful transmissions.

panels.title: NR_5057e 5G Residual BLER in PUSCH / UL resid BLER PUSCH [%]
BLER

panels.description:
This KPI shows the residual Block Error Ratio (BLER) for PUSCH. Residual BLER is defined as the ratio between the number of failed transmissions after the MAX harq retransmission reached and the number of packets to transmit, that is, the 1st HARQ transmissions.
In real-time monitoring, the HARQ feedback might be received in a diferent measurement period than the initial transmission. For that reason, the initial transmissions in the formula are calculated as the successful transmissions plus the unsuccessful transmissions.

panels.description:
This KPI shows the average estimated F1 round trip delay between CU and MAC DU, measured on gNB and per DU. It is the time:
- Starting when the PDCP PDU packet is sent by CU over F1 (PDCP PDU packet has left CU)
Then, this PDCP PDU packet is going until MAC PDU (of DU). When the 1st segment is ready to be sent on the air for the first time (excluding repetitions), the MAC PDU sends a DDDS to CU.
- And ending when the DDDS (sent by the MAC PDU) message is received by CU over F1 to acknowledge the packet (removed from CU buffer).
Note:
- We can consider that the time to process the DDDS message is equivalent to a PDU message received on CU over F1 and the PDU was sent by MAC PDU.
panels.title: NR_5050b 5G Average estimated F1 round trip delay between CU and MAC DU / Avg F1 rnd trip delay CU MAC DU [ms]

panels.description:
This KPI shows the average estimated X2 round trip delay between CU and MAC eNB cell, measured on gNB and per X2. It is the time:
- starting when the PDCP PDU packet is sent by CU over X2 until RLC multiplexed packet in the MAC PDU (of cell of eNB) to be transmitted in the air for the first time
- and ending when the DDDS (sent by the MAC PDU) message is received by CU over X2 to acknowledge the packet (removed from CU buffer).
Note: We can consider that the time to process the DDDS message is equivalent to a PDU message received on CU over X2 and the PDU was sent by MAC PDU (of cell of eNB).
panels.title: NR_5051b 5G NSA Average estimated X2 round trip delay between CU and MAC eNB / NSA Avg X2 rnd trip delay CU MAC eNB [ms]
